@node "intro" "Introduction"

What does it do?  Simple.

Have you ever used your terminal software to call a friend or a phone
that is always busy?  I have.

Have you ever called one of those "dial your card number" lines that only
accept tone dialing, from a pulse-only phone?  I have.

Problems like that are common on countries like mine, where the phone
services haven't reached a standard yet.  So, since I bought a modem I
was looking for a simple program that would let me dial directly from my
computer keyboard.  As I haven't found it, I decided to try to make my
own.  And here it is.
@endnode

@node "require" "Requirements"

In order to use Dialer, you need the following:

Hardware:

- An Amiga computer
- A modem connected to the serial port

Software

- WB 2.0 or greater
- Siesta.font on your FONTS: directory
  (this font is supplied within this archive)

Besides these items, a phone line should be very useful... 8^)
@endnode

@node "usage" "Using it    "

There are two ways you can use Dialer:

  @{"Window/Mouse operation" link "window" 0}

  @{"Keyboard operation    " link "keyboard" 0}
@endnode

@node "config" "Configuration"

To configure the program, you can use the following Tooltypes on its icon:

@{b}INIT1@{ub}
This is the command that you send to the modem to initialize it.  The
default value is "atz".

@{b}INIT2@{ub}
This is the modem command used to tell the modem to ignore the dialtone when
dialing.  Default value is "atx3".

@{b}MODE@{ub}
This is the mode at which the modem will be set at startup.  Possible values
are "p" for pulse dialing and "t" for tone dialing.  You must use @{b}lowercase@{ub}
characters only.  Default value is "p" (pulse dialing).

@{b}WINX@{ub}
This defines the X coordinate of the top-left corner of the window. Default
value is 100.

@{b}WINY@{ub}
This defines the Y coordinate of the top-left corner of the window. Default
value is 11.

@{b}PHONE@{ub}
This is a time-saver.  When you startup the program you will have instant
access to this phone number using the BACKSPACE key.  (See @{"keyboard" link "keyboard" 0})

@{b}@{fg shine}IMPORTANT@{ub}@{fg text}: As the program looks for the "Dialer.info" file inside the
           current directory to get these tooltypes from, you should @{b}NOT@{ub}
           rename the program.
@endnode

