@node "window" "Window/Mouse Operation"

When you star Dialer, it opens its screen on the Workbench. It looks like
this:

    @{"String gadget     " link "str_gadget" 0}
    @{"  1  " link "but_number" 0} @{"  2  " link "but_number" 0} @{"  3  " link "but_number" 0}
    @{"  4  " link "but_number" 0} @{"  5  " link "but_number" 0} @{"  6  " link "but_number" 0}
    @{"  7  " link "but_number" 0} @{"  8  " link "but_number" 0} @{"  9  " link "but_number" 0}
    @{" T/P " link "but_tp" 0} @{"  0  " link "but_number" 0} @{" ATH " link "but_ath" 0}

(Click on a button to know more about it)
@endnode

@node "keyboard" "Keyboard Operation"

Dialer can be operated from the keyboard. Here are the keys used and their
functions:

@{b}Numeric keys (0-9)@{ub}
Pressing these keys is just like pressing the window's @{"numeric buttons" link "but_number" 0}.

@{b}SPACE@{ub}
It works like the @{"ATH button" link "but_ath" 0}, changing the hook state of the modem.

@{b}RETURN / ENTER@{ub}
Works like the @{"T/P button" link "but_tp" 0}, changing the dialing mode.

@{b}BACKSPACE@{ub}
Redials the last number dialed with the @{i}string dial@{ui} mode (see @{"String gadget" link "str_gadget" 0})
or the number configured in the "PHONE" tooltype (see @{"Configuration" link "config" 0})

@{b}TAB@{ub}
Activates the string gadget, and puts you on @{i}string dial@{ui} mode. (See
@{"String gadget" link "str_gadget" 0})

@{b}HELP@{ub}
Brings up the "About Dialer" window.

@{b}ESC@{ub}
Exits the program.
@endnode

@node "str_gadget" "String Gadget"

The string gadget at the top of the window is used to show the output of the
program. When you see an "OK" message inside it, it means that the modem is
ready for further commands.

Clicking on the string gadget will clear any text inside it and put you on
@{i}string dial@{ui} mode.  On this mode, you can enter a phone number and, as soon
as you finish typing it (with the ENTER or RETURN key), the program will do
two things:

- Store the number on memory, so you can redial it with just a single
  keypress later. (See @{"keyboard" link "keyboard" 0})

- Dial the number.

You should just use numbers on this mode, or else the program will show a
"Cannot dial!" message.  Alternatively, you can use commas (,) with the
numbers.  The comma is a "pause command".
@endnode

@node "but_number" "Numeric Buttons"

The numeric buttons act just like the numeric keys on an actual telephone.
The string gadget will show that the program is dialing the number.
@endnode

@node "but_ath" ""

The "ATH" button is used to control the hook state of the modem. Clicking on
it toggles between "On hook" and "Off hook" states.
@endnode

@node "but_tp" ""

The "T/P" button changes the dialing mode. Clicking on it will toggle
between "TONE" and "PULSE" modes.
@endnode

